@startuml C4_Concern_Resilience
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Cross-Cutting Concern - Fault Tolerance & Resilience

Boundary(resilience_patterns, "Resilience Patterns") {
    Component(circuit_breaker, "CircuitBreaker", "Resilience4j", "Fail fast")
    Component(retry_policy, "RetryPolicy", "Backoff", "Exponential retry")
    Component(bulkhead, "Bulkhead", "Isolation", "Resource limits")
    Component(timeout_policy, "TimeoutPolicy", "SLA", "Time limits")
    Component(fallback, "Fallback", "Alternative", "Default behavior")
}

Boundary(failure_detection, "Failure Detection") {
    Component(health_check, "HealthCheck", "Probe", "Service liveness")
    Component(metrics_monitor, "MetricsMonitor", "Observability", "Metric tracking")
    Component(failure_detector, "FailureDetector", "Algorithm", "Detect failures")
}

Boundary(recovery, "Recovery Strategies") {
    Component(checkpoint_recovery, "CheckpointRecovery", "State", "Resume from checkpoint")
    Component(replication, "Replication", "HA", "Replicate state")
    Component(failover, "Failover", "Automatic", "Switch to standby")
}

resilience_patterns --> failure_detection: Informed by
failure_detection --> recovery: Triggers
recovery --> resilience_patterns: Adjusts strategy

Note as N1
Resilience Stack:
1. Circuit Breaker: Fail fast on repeated errors
2. Retry: Exponential backoff (2s, 4s, 8s, 16s)
3. Bulkhead: Limit concurrent requests
4. Timeout: Abort stuck operations
5. Fallback: Degrade gracefully

Monitoring:
- Health checks every 30s
- Circuit breaker state
- Error rates & latency
- Recovery time
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
